ConfigMap:  CM

sesitive : secret
non-secure Information:  ConfigMap

1. Namespace scope
2. As mount and ENV variable
3. CM modify then Pod  rollout .

____________________________________

NOte: there is no type of configmap

Example-1:

kubectl create cm cka --from-literal=proxyip=192.168.1.100
kubectl get cm

kubectl get cm cka -o yaml

kubectl set env deploy nginx --from configmap/cka    # To map cm value with pod/deployment

Now you see the cm value has been mapped into deployment  # kubectl edit deploy nginx

If anytime value gets changed then you have to restart the deployment
kubectl rollout restart deploy nginx
